I recently found myself needing to extract the file name but not file extension from a bunch of file paths and wanted to share a neat technique that I learnt to do it.
 I started with a bunch of Jupyter notebook files, which I listed usign the following command;
 $ find notebooks/ -maxdepth 1 -iname *ipynb notebooks/09_Predictions_sagemaker.ipynb notebooks/00_Environment.ipynb notebooks/05_Train_Evaluate_Model.ipynb notebooks/01_DataLoading.ipynb notebooks/05_SageMaker.ipynb notebooks/09_Predictions_sagemaker-Copy2.ipynb notebooks/09_Predictions_sagemaker-Copy1.ipynb notebooks/02_Co-Author_Graph.ipynb notebooks/04_Model_Feature_Engineering.ipynb notebooks/09_Predictions_scikit.ipynb notebooks/03_Train_Test_Split.ipynb   If we pick one of those files:
